{"id":"5590","name":"Siri HOOBS Manager","tagline":"Manage your HOOBS instance with Siri!","icon":"ios13 c4274264319 g59826","latest":"18029","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h1>Siri HOOBS Manager</h1>\n<h3>Manage your HOOBS instance with Siri!</h3>\n<p><img alt=\"HOOBS Logo\" src=\"https://hoobs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/weblogo_o.png\" title=\"Title\"></p>\n<p>What does this do? Well the answer is simple. This is a shortcut that allows you to manage your HOOBS instance using Siri and Natural Language. Here are the full feature sets!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Restart HOOBS (Homebridge service)</li>\n<li>Reboot your server</li>\n<li>Check the online status of your instance (is Homebridge running?)</li>\n<li>Update HOOBS</li>\n<li>Check the CPU temperature on your server (Linux and Pi users only)</li>\n<li>You can delete your configuration by telling it to \"restore the shortcut\" this deletes your configuration.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you ever need a little help on what you can do, you can say \"Help Me\" and Siri will tell you all the available actions :)</p>\n<h3>Coming Soon...</h3>\n<p>The roadmap for this shortcut is rather clear. As this is the initial release, there is a bit of room to grow. Here is what we have planned!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Diagnostic Tool (to help you assess problems)</li>\n<li>A repair instance tool </li>\n<li>Backup feature</li>\n</ul>\n<p>this shortcut uses LightningEmbed for updating! no need to install an alternate updater.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - June 17, 2020, 3:41 p.m.</strong></p>"}